<div id="pf5a4f" class="pf w7e h360" data-page-no="5a4f"><div class="pc pc5a4f w7e h360"><div class="t m1637 x6f ha5 y2ffa ff1 fs1c fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lesson 11 </div><div class="t m5 x42 ha5 y31b1 ff1 fs1c fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">î˜‰</div><div class="t m562 x62 ha5 y30ef ff1 fs1c fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">September 5-11 </div><div class="t me76 x1d h13b y2f02 ff1 fs43 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Guidelines </div><div class="t m1157 x6d h13b y2a24 ff1 fs43 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to Christian Character </div><div class="t m272a x6f h18e y20e ff7 fs24 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sabbath Afternoon </div><div class="t m1921 x34 h51 y1395 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">READ FOR THIS WEEK&apos;S STUDY: Titus 2:1-10. </div><div class="t maf9 x59 h51 y178e ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MEMORY TEXT: &quot;Show yourself in all respects a model of </div><div class="t mce3 x59 h51 y8b3 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">good deeds, and in your teaching show integrity, gravity, </div><div class="t mce3 x59 h51 y12ce ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and sound speech that cannot be censured&quot; (Titus 2:7, 8, </div><div class="t mc37 x59 h51 y20c6 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">RSV). </div><div class="t m36f x59 h51 y218b ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">KEY THOUGHT: Christian character stems from fellowship </div><div class="t med9 x34 h51 y18fe ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with Christ that manifests itself in loving, loyal attitudes and </div><div class="t m407 x34 h51 y13c0 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">deeds. </div><div class="t m9a1 x59 h51 y1313 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">CHRISTIAN BEHAVIOR is very much a part of sound </div><div class="t m2eb x34 h51 y134 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">doctrine (Titus 2:1). Attitudes and behavior that God can </div><div class="t m131c x34 h51 y657 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">accept are inseparably linked with holiness. We are not holy </div><div class="t m1105 x34 h51 y79b ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">by nature; holiness (sanctification) is Christ&apos;s gift to us by the </div><div class="t mb97 x34 h51 y1d59 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Holy Spirit (1 Peter 1:1, 2; 2 Thess. 2:13). Holiness is evi-</div><div class="t m63b x34 h51 y1449 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">denced through Christlike living. </div><div class="t m264 x59 h51 y90e ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The book of Hebrews speaks of &quot;holiness, without which </div><div class="t ma9 x34 h51 y10a1 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">no man shall see the Lord&quot; (Heb. 12:14). Holiness is righteous-</div><div class="t m77a x34 h51 y19f9 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ness. (See </div><div class="t mf30 x7c h3b y1463 ff6 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Thoughts From the Mount of Blessing, </div><div class="t mcff xe1 h51 y2054 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. 18.) Right-</div><div class="t m668 x34 h51 y16d8 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">eousness (holiness), as Jesus defined it in the Sermon on the </div><div class="t m778 x34 h51 y36e ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Mount (Matthew 5), is a pure attitude of mind that manifests </div><div class="t m856 x34 h51 yd81 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">itself in outward acts acceptable to God. Paul taught that </div><div class="t m27c x34 h51 y114f ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ died, &quot;that the righteousness of the law might be ful-</div><div class="t m264 x34 h51 y19ee ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">filled in us&quot; (Rom. 8:3, 4). Christ within is righteousness or </div><div class="t m1080 x34 h51 yf8d ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">holiness within. The result is holy thoughts, words, and acts </div><div class="t m1669 x34 h51 y1ede ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">directed by the Holy Spirit. </div><div class="t m2174 x34 h51 y13a5 ff1 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">76 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
